@ourlegacy Spring/Summer 2027 collection is an Anglophilic love letter to the British subcultures that shaped the second half of the 20th century, brought to life by filmmaker, DJ, and musician Don Letts. Visitors to the brand's Paris showroom experience the collection through a vintage Walkman, with Letts' unmistakable voice guiding them through a ten-minute history of punk, reggae, mods, and New Romantics. Following last season's "Just Clothes," SS27 is one of Our Legacy's rare theme-driven collections, translating British dress codes into the brand's signature generous silhouettes and quietly elevated wardrobe staples.⁠
⁠
The collection also includes a collaboration with Fred Perry, a label whose tennis shirts became staples of mods, punks, and ska culture. Reworking polos, scarves, and over-washed silk cardigans, the partnership celebrates a shared appreciation for enduring design and subcultural authenticity. "We've always been drawn to people who, like Fred Perry himself, do things their own way," says Fred Perry managing director Richard Gilmore, while Our Legacy co-founder Cristopher Nying describes the brand as a lasting beacon of London style.⁠

@songforthemute and @adidas returned to Paris Fashion Week to unveil the latest chapter of their ongoing partnership. Presented on the runway, the collection continued the duo's signature approach to sportswear, pairing adidas heritage with SONG FOR THE MUTE's distinct perspective on texture, proportion and craftsmanship.⁠
⁠
Swipe through for a closer look at the collection.⁠

